    <!-- How It Works Guide Modal -->
    <div class="modal" id="guide-modal">
        <div class="modal-overlay" onclick="closeGuide()"></div>
        <div class="modal-content large">
            <div class="modal-header">
                <h2>📖 How Zero Downtime Works</h2>
                <button class="modal-close" onclick="closeGuide()">&times;</button>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body guide-content">
                <!-- Overview -->
                <div class="guide-section">
                    <h3>🎯 Overview</h3>
                    <p>Zero Downtime is an intelligent AI-powered DevOps automation system that monitors your production environment 24/7, automatically detects issues, diagnoses root causes using AI, generates fixes, and intelligently assigns them to available team members.</p>
                    <div class="guide-highlight">
                        <strong>Result:</strong> 90% faster incident resolution (15 min vs 2-4 hrs) with 67% auto-fix success rate, saving $117K/year in developer time.
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- The Workflow -->
                <div class="guide-section">
                    <h3>🔄 End-to-End Automated Workflow</h3>
                    <div class="workflow-steps">
                        <div class="workflow-step">
                            <div class="workflow-step-number">1</div>
                            <div class="workflow-step-content">
                                <h4>🔍 Continuous Monitoring</h4>
                                <p><strong>What happens:</strong> System monitors multiple data sources in real-time</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li><strong>GitHub:</strong> Repository events, pipeline failures, deployment issues</li>
                                    <li><strong>Observability Tools:</strong> Datadog metrics, AWS CloudWatch logs, Rollbar errors, New Relic APM, Sentry exceptions</li>
                                    <li><strong>Application Logs:</strong> Batch jobs stuck, API timeouts, database issues</li>
                                    <li><strong>Azure DevOps:</strong> Work item status, sprint progress, build failures</li>
                                </ul>
                                <p class="workflow-example">📌 <strong>Example:</strong> Detects batch job stuck in "pending" state for 2+ hours</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="workflow-step">
                            <div class="workflow-step-number">2</div>
                            <div class="workflow-step-content">
                                <h4>📋 Automatic Ticket Creation</h4>
                                <p><strong>What happens:</strong> System creates a structured ADO work item</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Generates descriptive title and detailed description</li>
                                    <li>Tags with appropriate labels (bug, performance, critical)</li>
                                    <li>Links to relevant logs and error traces</li>
                                    <li>Assigns to correct project and sprint</li>
                                </ul>
                                <p class="workflow-example">📌 <strong>Example:</strong> Creates ticket "AB#1618776: Batch Job Stuck in Pending"</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="workflow-step">
                            <div class="workflow-step-number">3</div>
                            <div class="workflow-step-content">
                                <h4>🧠 AI-Powered Root Cause Analysis</h4>
                                <p><strong>What happens:</strong> AI analyzes the issue with full context</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li><strong>Code Analysis:</strong> Reads relevant service files, models, controllers</li>
                                    <li><strong>Git History:</strong> Checks recent commits that touched affected files</li>
